statements: SELECT * FROM bone_structure_force_distribution;
SELECT bone_name, force_distribution FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE force_distribution > 50;
SELECT * FROM bone_structure_force_distribution ORDER BY bone_name DESC;
SELECT bone_name, injury_prevention_measurements FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE bone_id = 3;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_bones FROM bone_structure_force_distribution;
SELECT bone_name, force_distribution FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE force_distribution > 50 ORDER BY force_distribution DESC
SELECT * FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE bone_name LIKE 'Femur%'
SELECT bone_id, bone_name, injury_prevention_measurements FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE bone_id BETWEEN 10 AND 20
SELECT bone_name, force_distribution, injury_prevention_measurements FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE force_distribution < 30 ORDER BY bone_name ASC
SELECT * FROM bone_structure_force_distribution WHERE force_distribution IS NOT NULL
SELECT * FROM ForceDistribution;
SELECT bone_structure, force_applied FROM ForceDistribution;
SELECT * FROM InjuryPrevention WHERE injury_type='fracture';
SELECT id, prevention_method FROM InjuryPrevention ORDER BY study_id DESC;
SELECT id, bone_structure, force_applied FROM ForceDistribution WHERE force_applied > 100;
SELECT * FROM ForceDistribution WHERE bone_structure = 'Femur';
SELECT id, bone_structure FROM ForceDistribution WHERE force_applied > 100 ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT f.id, f.bone_structure, i.injury_type, i.prevention_method FROM ForceDistribution f JOIN InjuryPrevention i ON f.id = i.study_id WHERE f.force_applied BETWEEN 50 AND 100;
SELECT f.id, f.bone_structure, i.injury_type FROM ForceDistribution f LEFT JOIN InjuryPrevention i ON f.id = i.study_id WHERE i.injury_type LIKE '%Fracture%' ORDER BY f.id;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_injuries, AVG(f.force_applied) AS avg_force FROM ForceDistribution f INNER JOIN InjuryPrevention i ON f.id = i.study_id WHERE i.injury_type = 'Sprain';
SELECT * FROM BoneStructure;
SELECT name, type FROM BoneStructure WHERE study_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT id, injury_type, prevention_method FROM InjuryPrevention WHERE injury_date < '2022-05-01' ORDER BY injury_date DESC;
SELECT id, bone_id, force_value, measurement_date FROM ForceMeasurement WHERE force_value >= 100 ORDER BY measurement_date ASC;
SELECT * FROM ForceMeasurement JOIN BoneStructure ON ForceMeasurement.bone_id = BoneStructure.id WHERE BoneStructure.type = 'Femur' AND ForceMeasurement.measurement_date >= '2022-06-01';
SELECT * FROM BoneStructure;
SELECT id, name, type, study_date FROM BoneStructure WHERE type = 'Femur';
SELECT bs.name, fp.injury_type FROM BoneStructure bs JOIN InjuryPrevention fp ON bs.id = fp.id;
SELECT bs.id, fm.force_value, fm.measurement_date FROM BoneStructure bs JOIN ForceMeasurement fm ON bs.id = fm.bone_id WHERE fm.force_value > 100;
SELECT bs.id, bs.name, fm.force_value FROM BoneStructure bs LEFT JOIN ForceMeasurement fm ON bs.id = fm.bone_id;
SELECT * FROM bone_structures;
SELECT sensor_name, accuracy FROM force_sensors ORDER BY sensor_name DESC;
SELECT sensor_id, sensor_type FROM force_sensors WHERE accuracy > 0.9;
SELECT bone_name, bone_type, mass FROM bone_structures WHERE bone_density < 0.5;
SELECT * FROM force_measurements WHERE force_reading > 100 ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT * FROM force_sensors ORDER BY sensor_name DESC LIMIT 3;
SELECT sensor_name, sensor_type FROM force_sensors WHERE accuracy > 0.95;
SELECT bone_name, bone_type, mass FROM bone_structures WHERE bone_density < 0.6 ORDER BY bone_name ASC;
SELECT sensor_id, sensor_name, insertion_location FROM force_sensors WHERE sensor_type = 'Handheld' AND accuracy >= 0.9;
SELECT force_reading, timestamp FROM force_measurements JOIN injury_records ON force_measurements.bone_id = injury_records.bone_id WHERE injury_type = 'Fracture';
SELECT * FROM ForceSensors;
SELECT sensor_id, sensor_type, sensor_location FROM ForceSensors WHERE sensor_accuracy > 0.9;
SELECT * FROM BoneStructures ORDER BY structure_name DESC;
SELECT structure_id, structure_type, structure_size FROM BoneStructures WHERE structure_type = 'Femur' AND structure_size = 'Large';
SELECT participant_id, participant_name, participant_age, participant_gender FROM ResearchParticipants WHERE participant_age >= 30 ORDER BY participant_name ASC;
SELECT sensor_id, sensor_type, sensor_location FROM ForceSensors WHERE sensor_accuracy > 0.9 ORDER BY sensor_type DESC LIMIT 5
SELECT * FROM BoneStructures WHERE structure_size = 'Small' OR structure_type = 'Femur' ORDER BY structure_id ASC
SELECT measurement_id, force_value, measurement_date FROM ForceMeasurements WHERE force_value BETWEEN 10 AND 20 ORDER BY measurement_date DESC
SELECT * FROM ResearchParticipants WHERE participant_age > 30 AND participant_gender = 'Female' ORDER BY participant_name ASC
SELECT * FROM StudyResults WHERE force_value > 100 ORDER BY result_date DESC, participant_id ASC
